adrienne murphy center for latin american studies jump to navigation stanford university center for latin american studies search this site home people ma students adrienne murphy adrienne murphy people overview clas affiliated faculty tinker professors nabuco scholars visiting scholars ma students clas staff also see stanford directory adrienne murphy biography adrienne murphy originally from dallas texas graduated from the university of notre dame in 2009 while pursuing her ba in history and spanish she spent a semester studying in santiago chile where she first fell in love with latin america she spent her time in chile learning about the political economic and social history of chile and volunteering in a homeless shelter for elderly males this experience drove adrienne to add a concentration in latin american studies upon her return to notre dame so that she could continue to explore the history of the region after graduating adrienne joined teach for america and moved to mcallen texas where she spent two years teaching middle school reading and social studies at a charter school miles from the border while living in south texas adrienne developed a strong interest in the social impact of immigration policy specifically the impact of this policy on education in the borderlands an interest that she hopes to continue to explore while at stanford in her spare time adrienne likes to read watch movies and is an avid sports fan last updated august 29 2011 11 12am main menu about degree programs visiting faculty & scholar programs grants & fellowships people events newsletter giving to clas secondary menu stanford home ica clasp login contact stanford university center for latin american studies bolivar house 582 alvarado row stanford ca 94305 usa phone 650.723 4444 fax 650.723 9822 stanford university terms of use copyright complaints
